column5: Thats a nice sharp knife.  By the way, I am going to have nightmares tonight.
i now have a new hero. no  blood on his shirt or jeans???   ill bet he didnt miss dinner?  awesum!!
Not a hunter myself...but I still enjoy watching a pro at work. I wonder how many he has done to get that good?
~~~Okay time to go shopping some Garlic, Onions, Sage, Pepper corn, Tomatoes, have I forgotten anything, Great Vid. Wonder how fast he can be out of season with MNR closing in.
Impressive, but....... That's obviously a 'southern' deer. Not much bigger than an adult goat + very thin hide.
He's not that good! he only beat me by about 17 minutes and 3 seconds  Actually learned a lot from that though, next time I'll use a knife
Pretty impressive. Looked like a medium size dog though. I'm sure he could post a similar time with a much larger deer however LOL.  Might have to review his technique for next fall.
if you can skin and clean a deer in 20 mins with your bare hands Cliff, you are my hero !!!
Yeah,my thoughts exactly. Cripes I drag that one a mile or two, whole.  Impressive knife work though.
